                <head>No. 123.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hitt</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1878-07-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 17, 1878</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Evarts</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Am told at foreign office, France, where monetary conference is to be held,
                    should issue invitations. She will do so only on our request <pb facs="0241"
                        n="179" xml:id="pg_179"/> Shall I request to invite for tenth August? France
                    concurs as to time and place. She also wishes speedy exchange ratification
                    metrical convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HITT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
